# RFC-windows PR-5 — normalise line endings to LF on checkout so `format:check`
# (prettier, endOfLine: lf) is meaningful on Windows CI runners. Without this,
# a Windows checkout with `core.autocrlf=true` stores LF but checks out CRLF,
# red-ing prettier on every file. `eol=lf` forces LF in the working tree on
# all platforms; CI gets a clean LF tree, local Windows dev trees stay LF too.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalise (CRLF conversion corrupts them).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
*.webp binary
*.svg binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.eot binary
*.wasm binary
*.sqlite binary
*.db binary
*.zip binary
*.tar.gz binary
*.gz binary
